Capital One Says ING Deal Includes $270 Million Termination Fee

-- B y   L a u r a   M a r c i n e k
-- 
2011-06-22T21:12:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/capital-one-says-ing-deal-includes-270-million-termination-fee.html
Capital One Financial Corp. (COF) , the top
performing stock this year in the KBW Bank Index, said it may
have to pay a termination fee of $270 million if its $9 billion
deal to buy ING Direct USA falters.  The fee was disclosed by  Chevy Chase , Maryland-based
Capital One in a regulatory filing today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Laura Marcinek in New York at 
 Lmarcinek3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  